  "A hospital implements a new hand-washing protocol. Before the protocol, the infection rate was 8 per 1,000 patients. After, it dropped to 3 per 1,000. The NNT (number needed to treat) for the hand-washing protocol is:": "",
  "5": "",
  "200": "",
  "100": "",
  "500": "",
  "ARR = 8/1000 − 3/1000 = 5/1000 = 0.005. NNT = 1/0.005 = 200. For every 200 patients exposed to the protocol, one infection is prevented.": "",
  "A marathon runner's finishing times over 10 races are: 3:10, 3:08, 3:15, 3:12, 3:11, 3:09, 3:14, 3:10, 3:13, 3:11 (hours:minutes). The coach says the runner is 'very consistent.' Which statistic best supports this claim?": "",
